{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"627885de-c87f-45db-ab36-3223f282f48c","content":"Analyzing a .dmp file is outside the scope of the available `dump-collect` skill (which only covers **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them).\n\nHere's how to analyze your crash dump:\n\n### Tools for Analysis\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** — .NET-specific interactive analyzer\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-app.dmp\n   # Then use commands like: clrstack, pe (print exception), dso\n   ```\n\n2. **LLDB** (Linux) — with the SOS debugging extension\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb -c your-app.dmp\n   # Then: clrstack, pe, dumpheap, etc.\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg** (Windows) — with SOS or MEX extensions\n\n### Quick triage commands (inside `dotnet-dump analyze`)\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `pe` | Print last exception |\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack |\n| `threads` | List all threads |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and start an interactive analysis session with your dump file? If so, share the path to the `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aad6f840-6126-4c87-bdd0-fc43009d424f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So I should NOT invoke that skill.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":423,"requestId":"D80D:13B160:600B3B4:67FF95E:69FBF1AB"},"id":"3f104b21-99fb-4e41-bcf8-a0d65bad6f0d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:58:15.620Z","parentId":"1f0a6a9c-053a-4cf2-b01e-8e4b5e88c222"}
